<div id="review_171504175" class="review" itemprop="reviews" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Review">
  <link itemprop="url" href="https://www.goodreads.com/review/show/171504175" />
    <a title="C.J. Noonan" class="left imgcol" href="/user/show/5303977-c-j-noonan"><img alt="C.J. Noonan" src="https://images.gr-assets.com/users/1310474483p2/5303977.jpg" /></a>

  <div class="left bodycol">
    <div class="reviewHeader uitext stacked">
        <a class="reviewDate createdAt right" href="/review/show/171504175?book_show_action=true">May 27, 2011</a>

      <span itemprop="author" itemscope itemtype="http://schema.org/Person">
        <a title="C.J. Noonan" class="user" itemprop="url" name="C.J. Noonan" href="/user/show/5303977-c-j-noonan">C.J. Noonan</a>
      </span>

        rated it
        <span class=" staticStars notranslate" title="liked it"><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10">liked it</span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p10"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span><span size="15x15" class="staticStar p0"></span></span>



        

    </div>


        <div class="reviewText stacked">
              <span id="reviewTextContainer171504175" class="readable"
              >
            
<span id="freeTextContainer9822900783878514419">Read Daughter of Fortune by Isabel Allende, another book about a woman in Gold Rush times in California. The story of the protagonist, a young girl raised by an English merchant marine family in Valparaiso, Chile, begins in the early 1800&apos;s. The reader learns about the thriving merchant marine enterprises of the British in South America. The girl falls in love at 16 with a poor, handsome, self-educated Chilean and follows him to California at the beginning of the Gold Rush 1849. The rest of the </span>
  <span id="freeText9822900783878514419" style="display:none">Read Daughter of Fortune by Isabel Allende, another book about a woman in Gold Rush times in California. The story of the protagonist, a young girl raised by an English merchant marine family in Valparaiso, Chile, begins in the early 1800's. The reader learns about the thriving merchant marine enterprises of the British in South America. The girl falls in love at 16 with a poor, handsome, self-educated Chilean and follows him to California at the beginning of the Gold Rush 1849. The rest of the novel treats her experiences in California, disguised as a young man, searching for her lover. Interesting to find out details about the Gold Rush, but some of the plot is predictable.</span>
  <a data-text-id="9822900783878514419" href="#" onclick="swapContent($(this));; return false;">...more</a>

          </span>
        </div>


